Vehicular movement alongÂ the Ife-Ibadan Expressway was thrown into chaos on Thursday afternoon following a fire incident involving a truck and two other vehicles along the road.
Although the cause of the fire incident could not be immediately ascertained, however, an eyewitness, who spoke to our correspondent said she feared many people may have been trapped in the inferno.
The Administrative Officer of Osun State Fire Service, Fatai Aremu, confirmed the incident and said his men had been deployed to the scene.